<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mi> 0.5 s, 1 s. </m:mi>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable> 
</m:math>
</para>

<para id="element-35">
This means that particle is twice at the origin at t = 0.5 s and t = 1 s. Now,
</para>
<para id="element-36">
<m:math display="block"> 
<m:mtable columnalign="left"> 

<m:mtr> 
<m:mtd>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mo> ( </m:mo>
<m:mi> t </m:mi>
<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mi> 0.5 s</m:mi>
<m:mo> ) </m:mo>
<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mn> 4 </m:mn>
<m:mi> t </m:mi>
<m:mn> - </m:mn>
<m:mn> 3 </m:mn>
<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mn> 4 </m:mn>
